step :
1) pip install virtualenv --> installation of virtual evnironment
2) python -m venv env_name --> set up of virtual evnironment
3) pip install django --> installation of Django
4) env_name\Scripts\activate.bat --> activate virtual evnironment
5) django-admin startproject name_Of_project --> create a new project
6) cd name_Of_project
7) py manage.py startapp app_name --> create new app in project
8) code . --> open VS code
9) setting --> installed_app --> name_of_app
10) py manage.py migrate --> for activate databases
11) py manage.py makemigrations --> for apply databases changes
12) py manage.py createsuperuser
13) urls.py -> path of our file/logic
    urlpattern = [
        path("name_of_url\", views.home)
    ]
14) views.py --> def home --> templates/ database
15) models/ template/ static file